# Host

## Summary
Host models someone hosting the event — a bride, groom, or one of their parents. It extends Person, inheriting `fullName`, `photo`, and the computed `photoURL`, and adds a `role` enum restricted to the six `HOST_ROLES` (Bride, Groom, and each of their mothers and fathers) shown beneath the name in its gold-badged embedded view; the module also exports the `HOST_ROLES` list and the `RoleField` enum field. The Table Seating Planner links hosts via `hosts = linksToMany(Host)` and joins their names into a computed `hostNames` string for the event header.

## Import
```js
import { Host } from '../host';
```

## Usage
Host is a card, so consuming cards link to it — the same wiring the planner uses:

```js
import { CardDef, field, linksToMany } from 'https://cardstack.com/base/card-api';
import { Host } from '../host';

export class EventHeader extends CardDef {
  @field hosts = linksToMany(() => Host);
}
```

## Template Usage
```handlebars
<@fields.hosts @format='embedded' />
```
Renders each host as an avatar row with their name, role, and a "Host" badge.
